Graph properties besides {@link #isDirected() directedness} do not affect equality.
addition.255: * For example, two graphs may be considered equal even if one allows self-loops and the other
addition.256: * doesn't. Additionally, the order in which nodes or edges are added to the graph, and the order
addition.257: * in which they are iterated over, are irrelevant.
